 doll will be brought to you - glass optional.  %0a%3c %0a%3c !! %25center%25%25color=#008080%25Gallery%0a%3c || %25newwin thumb%25https://i.imgur.com/377rkGU.png || %25newwin thumb%25https://i.imgur.com/NvZ1OW7.png || %25newwin thumb%25https://i.imgur.com/4n8Jk9N.png || %25newwin thumb%25https://i.imgur.com/qXucEMQ.png || %25newwin thumb%25https://i.imgur.com/eogRrb7.png ||%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c !! %25center%25%25color=#008080%25Rules For The Forgotten Midnight%25%25%0a%3c These rules are explained by Pam when a member first joins. There are no exceptions to the rules as presented and no excuses are allowed. Ignorance is not an exception to the rules in this area, failure to follow the rules will lead to being banned from the property for 1 month, 3 months, and permanently.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c %0a%3c Rule 1: You must request a blood doll from a server and pay for the time. You cannot just grab servers or blood dolls for yourself. [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c Rule 2: No feeding off of guests unless your server is alerted that you will do so and both parties agree to the feeding. [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c No feeding of unwilling partners. [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c Rule 3: No feeding off of the Servers. This is non-negotiable. [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c Rule 4: Do not bring mortals (non-Mortal+ that is) to the bar. [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c Rule 5: There is to be no fighting within the bar or on the property. If you cannot work out your issues in a civilized way you will be escorted roughly off the property by the security staff. [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c Rule 6: If you break it (or kill it) you buy it. [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c %0a%3c (:tableend:)   %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:table valign=top:)%0a%3c (:cellnr width=700 colspan=2 align=center:)%0a%3c ! %25center%25%25color=#008080%25 Supernatural Effect or Merits%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!%25center%25%25color=#008080%25STAFF: 1 (Servers: Socialize)%0a%3c Effect: Your character has a crew of workers or assistants at her disposal. They may be housekeepers, designers, research assistants, animators, thugs, or whatever else makes sense. For every dot in this Merit, choose one type of assistant, and one Skill. At any reasonable time, her staff can take action using that Skill. These actions automatically garner a single success.  While not useful in contested actions, this guarantees success on minor, mundane activities.%0a%3c Note that you may have employees or human packmates without requiring the Staff Merit. Staff simply adds mechanical advantage for those groups.%0a%3c %0a%3c (:tableend:)   %0a%3c %0a%3c (:include GameRef.Directorycity:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
